// src/pages/brands/cafe.astro
// GE Café brand pillar (~1.8k words). Built 2026-05-11. Tone reference:
// brands/marvel.astro pattern adapted to GE Café's mid-luxury, US-designed
// (Louisville KY), commercial-inspired styling tier. Voice discipline:
// position Café in the GE hierarchy (Profile → Café → Monogram),
// 2018-2022 CVE28 ice maker auger motor pattern, hardware-customization
// (matte finishes + brushed bronze/copper/black/stainless handle kits)
// as cosmetic not functional, Haier ownership (since 2016) parts impact
// = none (GE Appliances US network intact), LA renovation-market kitchens
// in Pasadena / Glendale / Studio City as the demographic. Honest
// repair-vs-replace math: Café units are $2K-$6K each so repair almost
// always wins at typical service price points.
//
// Pillar URL was clear of redirect blocks (no matches in astro.config.mjs
// or public/_redirects). Direct write, no redirect cleanup needed.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/ge-cafe/";

const title = "GE Café Appliance Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "GE Café refrigerator, range, dishwasher & oven repair in LA. Same-day service, OEM parts. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What GE Café appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "The full current Café lineup. French door refrigerators (CVE28DP2NS1 and the CVE28 family — the dominant Café refrigerator we see in LA renovation kitchens), side-by-side and column refrigerators, freestanding and slide-in ranges (C2S950P2MS1 gas/induction dual-fuel, CHS950P2MS1 induction slide-in), wall ovens single and double (CTS70DP2NS1, CTS90DP3MD1 advantium), dishwashers (CWB70SP3MD1 third-rack stainless interior, CDT875P2NS1), cooktops gas/electric/induction (CGP9530SLSS gas with brass burners, CHP9530SJSS induction), microwaves both over-the-range and built-in (PVM9005SJSS advantium), and the matte-finish hood vents (UVH13013MSS and adjacent series). All Café finishes — matte white, matte black, matte slate, brushed stainless — receive the same service work; the matte coatings require different cleaning chemistry than stainless but the underlying mechanical and electrical components are identical."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does GE Café refrigerator repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. Common Café refrigerator repairs in our LA service area: ice maker auger motor $245-$385 (the dominant 2018-2022 CVE28 service item across hard-water zip codes — Pasadena, Glendale, Burbank, Studio City all hit this pattern); French door ice dispenser flap or chute service $185-$285; evaporator fan motor $245-$385; defrost heater or defrost thermostat $185-$345; water inlet valve $185-$285; control board $345-$525; compressor relay $185-$285; door gasket $185-$285. Sealed-system work (compressor, condenser, refrigerant) on an out-of-warranty Café French door runs $580-$880, and we'll walk you through repair-vs-replace math at that price point — though Café refrigerators are priced $3K-$5K new, so the math almost always favors repair through year 8-10. Parts ship from GE Appliances' US distribution network (Louisville, KY headquarters, multiple regional warehouses), typical 2-5 day lead time for less-common items, common wear parts on the truck for the dominant CVE28 / CDT / C2S / CTS series."
  },
  {
    q: "Is GE Café the same as GE Profile or GE Monogram?",
    a: "No — they're three distinct tiers in GE Appliances' US lineup, and the confusion is common. Hierarchy: GE Appliances (base/value tier) → GE Profile (mid-tier, mainstream luxury) → GE Café (mid-luxury, commercial-inspired styling) → GE Monogram (full luxury, panel-ready built-in, competes with Sub-Zero/Wolf). Café launched in 2009 as the visual statement tier — matte finishes, customizable hardware (handles and knobs swappable in brushed bronze, brushed copper, brushed stainless, brushed black), commercial-inspired range and refrigerator styling. Profile is more conventional in appearance (stainless or fingerprint-resistant, fixed hardware), priced below Café. Monogram is the fully built-in panel-ready tier at the top. Practical service implication: Café shares many internal parts with Profile (compressors, ice maker assemblies, igniters, control boards), so parts availability is excellent — substantially better than European luxury brands. Café also shares some components with Monogram at the high end of the Café range, particularly on column refrigerators and pro-style induction cooktops. If you bought Café for the look at a Monogram-class kitchen on a lower budget, that strategy is well-served on the parts side."
  },
  {
    q: "My GE Café ice maker stopped working — what's the likely cause?",
    a: "Three causes in roughly the order we find them on Café French door refrigerators in LA, and one is significantly more common than the others. (1) Ice maker auger motor failure — the dominant service item on 2018-2022 CVE28 French door fridges. The auger motor that drives ice from the bin to the dispenser chute fails around year 3-5 of service, and the failure rate runs higher in hard-water zip codes — which is most of LA's San Gabriel Valley, the Valley side of the hills, and inland service areas (Pasadena, Glendale, Burbank, Studio City, Sherman Oaks, Encino, San Gabriel itself). The municipal water in those areas is harder than the Westside, mineral buildup loads the auger mechanism faster, the motor fails earlier. Replacement runs $245-$385, often same-day when we stock the CVE28-family auger assemblies. (2) Water inlet valve — solenoid valve at the back of the fridge that admits water to the ice maker. Failure mode: no water reaching the ice mold, no ice production at all (vs auger motor failure which produces ice but can't dispense it). $185-$285 replacement. (3) Ice maker control module or thermostat. Less common but real, $185-$345 depending on which component. Symptoms differentiate the causes: bin full but dispenser dead = auger; mold empty = water valve; mold filling but no harvest = control module. Diagnostic identifies which on-site before parts get ordered."
  },
  {
    q: "Does Haier ownership affect GE Café parts availability?",
    a: "No — and this is one of the most common concerns Café owners ask about, so worth addressing directly. Haier acquired GE Appliances in 2016, but the practical service ecosystem stayed US-based. Café (along with Profile, Monogram, Hotpoint, and the rest of the GE Appliances lineup) remains designed, engineered, and largely manufactured in the United States, with the Louisville, Kentucky headquarters and US engineering teams intact. Parts distribution runs through GE Appliances' established US warehouse network — Louisville (KY), Selmer (TN), LaFayette (GA), and regional distribution centers — not through Haier's overseas channels. Lead times on common Café service parts are 2-5 days, frequently same-day or next-day on dominant wear items we stock on the truck (auger motors, water valves, igniters, control boards for the CVE28 / C2S / CTS / CDT series). The Haier change also did not affect the GE Appliances warranty network or the authorized service-technician training programs. Practical bottom line: Haier ownership is a corporate structure detail; service availability and parts supply for your Café appliance is among the best in the industry."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you match my GE Café's custom hardware finish during repair?",
    a: "Yes, and the hardware question is worth understanding because it comes up often. Café's hardware-customization system is cosmetic, not functional — the handles and knobs ship separately as a kit (brushed bronze, brushed copper, brushed stainless, brushed black are the four current US finishes), and you can swap them at any point without affecting the appliance's operation. We don't need to match hardware to do mechanical or electrical repair work — the handles and knobs come off easily, work happens on the underlying chassis, hardware goes back on. If a handle itself is damaged (rare — they're robust) or you want to change finish during service, the hardware kits are ordered separately through GE Appliances or authorized Café dealers, and we can coordinate the order while we're working on the unit. The matte cabinet finishes (matte white, matte black, matte slate) require different cleaning care than stainless during service — we use non-abrasive cleaners and avoid stainless-specific polish on matte surfaces. The matte finish itself is durable; cosmetic damage to it during service work is not a typical concern."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find official GE Café warranty info?",
    a: `Our technicians work independently of GE's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
  }
];

