<!-- 07 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Café jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Café service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Café CVE28DP2NS1 French door refrigerator, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Ice bin appeared full but dispenser produced nothing for the past 2 weeks. Owner heard a grinding sound from inside the door when pressing the dispenser paddle. Unit was 4 years old, installed in a 2020 kitchen renovation.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2018-2022 CVE28 ice maker auger motor failure. Pasadena municipal water hardness loaded the auger mechanism over 4 years of service; the motor that drives ice from the bin to the dispenser chute had failed. Ice production from the ice maker itself was normal — issue was the dispense path, not the make path.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Ice maker auger motor replacement with OEM GE part (in stock on truck for the CVE28 family). Cleared accumulated ice and mineral debris from the auger housing. Verified normal dispense operation through 5 test cycles.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $325 total. Same-day, 75 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Café C2S950P2MS1 dual-fuel range, Studio City</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Gas cooktop burners ignited fine; oven would not light. Owner heard the spark igniter clicking but no flame. Unit was 4 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Oven igniter weak — measured below the current draw threshold needed to open the gas safety valve. Spark module functioning correctly (audible click confirmed). Classic year-3-5 igniter wear pattern on Café gas-oven ranges.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Oven igniter replacement with OEM GE part (in stock on truck — igniters are dominant Café cooking service item). Verified normal bake and broil light-off, oven temperature pull-up to 350°F within design window.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, 60 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Café CDT875P2NS1 dishwasher, Glendale</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dishwasher started cycles normally but stopped draining at the end — leaving 1-2 inches of standing water in the tub. Owner had checked the filter and air gap herself, no debris found. Unit was 5 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Drain pump failed — pump motor not engaging when commanded by the control board. Verified control board sending the drain command (multimeter at pump connector). Pump motor open-circuit on continuity test.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Drain pump replacement with OEM GE part. Verified normal end-of-cycle drain and full water evacuation across two complete wash cycles. Inspected drain hose routing and air gap as a paired check while on-site — both clear.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $285 total. Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

